   "source": [
    "# DataFrame Inspection Milestone\n",
    "\n",
    "## Learning Objectives\n",
    "- Use `head()` to preview DataFrame contents\n",
    "- Use `info()` to understand structure and data types\n",
    "- Use `describe()` to summarize numeric data\n",
    "- Detect obvious data issues early\n",
    "- Build inspection habits before analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Principle:** Always inspect data before analyzing it!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Load Sample Datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "We'll work with two datasets to practice inspection methods."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load employees dataset\n",
    "df_employees = pd.read_csv('../data/raw/employees.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load books dataset\n",
    "df_books = pd.read_csv('../data/raw/books.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Datasets loaded successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 1. Inspecting Data with head()\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:** Quick visual preview of the first few rows\n",
    "\n",
    "**What it reveals:**\n",
    "- Column names\n",
    "- Sample values\n",
    "- Data alignment\n",
    "- Initial data quality check"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Default: shows first 5 rows\n",
    "print(\"Employees - First 5 rows (default):\")\n",
    "print(df_employees.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Custom: specify number of rows\n",
    "print(\"\\nEmployees - First 3 rows:\")\n",
    "print(df_employees.head(3))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Inspect books dataset\n",
    "print(\"\\nBooks - First 5 rows:\")\n",
    "print(df_books.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**What we learned from head():**\n",
    "- Column names are clear and descriptive\n",
    "- Data appears properly aligned\n",
    "- No obvious formatting issues in the preview\n",
    "- We can see the types of values in each column"
   ]
  }
 ],
