   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 2. Inspecting Structure with info()\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:** Understand DataFrame structure, data types, and memory usage\n",
    "\n",
    "**What it reveals:**\n",
    "- Number of rows and columns\n",
    "- Column names\n",
    "- Data types for each column\n",
    "- Non-null counts (identifies missing values)\n",
    "- Memory usage"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Inspect employees structure\n",
    "print(\"Employees DataFrame Info:\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
    "df_employees.info()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Inspect books structure\n",
    "print(\"\\nBooks DataFrame Info:\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
    "df_books.info()"
   ]
  },
  {
