    "- Data types: 2 object (text), 2 int64 (numbers)\n",
    "- Title and Author are text columns\n",
    "- Year and Pages are numeric columns"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 3. Summarizing Data with describe()\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:** Get statistical summary of numeric columns\n",
    "\n",
    "**What it reveals:**\n",
    "- Count: number of non-null values\n",
    "- Mean: average value\n",
    "- Std: standard deviation (spread)\n",
    "- Min: minimum value\n",
    "- 25%, 50%, 75%: quartiles (percentiles)\n",
    "- Max: maximum value"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Describe employees numeric columns\n",
    "print(\"Employees - Numeric Summary:\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
    "print(df_employees.describe())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Describe books numeric columns\n",
    "print(\"\\nBooks - Numeric Summary:\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
    "print(df_books.describe())"
   ]
  },
